  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "The specs check uncles by calling the `validate_header()` function. However if the uncle is from the previous hardfork, the `validate_header()` function from the previous hardfork should be used.\r\n\r\nThis issue is probably hypothetical because [no fork block has had uncles](https://etherscan.io/blocks/label/network-fork), higher order uncles are rare and uncles will cease to exist from the merge.",
