    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Closing as won't fix.\r\n\r\nThis situation only occurs with higher order uncles happening immediately after a fork. Uncles are fairly rare and a quick perusal of Etherscan shows that no such uncle has ever occurred.\r\n\r\nHandling this case correctly would needlessly complicate the spec to cover a hypothetical historical edgecase. Even writing a correct testcase would not be easy in the standard test frameworks we use.",
